{
  "stem": "19550.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 52.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But of course, he wouldn't go, because as the saying went in Yiddish, in America you can't be a Jew.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he refused.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But when it became physically impossible for him-- I say he came under this subterfuge, and then eventually, he realized that he, he may have to stay and, and eventually got stuck because the great power-hungry declared war on the United States.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And in fact, we were-- he finally managed to get immigration papers for us, and we were invited to come to the consulate in, in Budapest or the embassy.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- but it was already too late.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] However, what I started to say was that my mother also imparted to me and, and endowed me with one of the most important, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I would say, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] facts of my life.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She herself managed to construct for herself a very unique kind of synthesis between her Judaism and her, and her humanitarianism.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she managed to, to live in these two worlds, as I have, thanks to her being able to live in, in this perhaps bipolar world without feeling the, any dichotomy.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I feel myself perfectly integrated as a Jew and a human being without any either emotional or intellectual problems [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] resulting from being, so to say, one foot in, in the Jewish world and one foot in, in the world at large.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] Unfortunately, she, like so many of the Hungarian Jews, was murdered the day we arrived in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I've had five sisters, who were alive in 1944.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I actually had family-- my mother had two twin boys who died at the age of three to six months.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But there were six of us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was the only boy.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
